# Point at any PostgreSQL 16.
#
# ADMIN_DATABASE_URL is the OWNER/migrator role: it runs migrations, owns the
# tables and the append-only triggers, and creates the runtime role. Keep it out
# of the application runtime.
ADMIN_DATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres:postgres@localhost:5432/catalog

# DATABASE_URL is the least-privileged runtime role the authority uses. It can
# append+read events and mutate the projection, but cannot UPDATE/DELETE/TRUNCATE
# events or disable the triggers.
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://app:app@localhost:5432/catalog

# If neither is set, `npm test` boots an embedded PostgreSQL 16 automatically.

# --- Configuration validation (Phase 3 Stage 3.1) ---------------------------
# Config is loaded + validated centrally (src/config/env.ts), failing fast and
# reporting EVERY problem at once. Error messages reference variable NAMES only,
# never their values, so a connection string's password cannot leak into logs.
#
# Required: DATABASE_URL (the runtime role). ADMIN_DATABASE_URL is optional and
# falls back to DATABASE_URL for a single-role dev setup (production should keep
# them distinct).
#
# Secret-file indirection (Docker / Unraid secrets): for any variable NAME you may
# instead set NAME_FILE to a file path; the value is read from that file (a single
# trailing newline is stripped). Setting both NAME and NAME_FILE is rejected.
#   DATABASE_URL_FILE=/run/secrets/database_url
#   ADMIN_DATABASE_URL_FILE=/run/secrets/admin_database_url
#
# --- Key custodian selection (Phase 3 Stage 3.2) ----------------------------
# createCustodian()/custodianFromEnv() (src/core/crypto/custodian-factory.ts) turn
# validated config into a KeyCustodian. The system depends only on the interface, so
# swapping the production custodian is a config change. Unknown modes FAIL CLOSED.
#
# CUSTODIAN_MODE: memory | file        (required)
#   memory = in-process dev/test custodian; file = FileCustodian reference harness.
# COMPLETION_SECRET (or COMPLETION_SECRET_FILE): the HMAC attestation secret shared
#   out-of-band with the DB (crypto_config). Required for all modes.
CUSTODIAN_MODE=memory
COMPLETION_SECRET=change-me-shared-with-the-database
#
# For CUSTODIAN_MODE=file, also set:
#   CUSTODIAN_KEYSTORE_DIR  keystore root (keep on a volume separate from DB backups)
#   CUSTODIAN_KEK (or CUSTODIAN_KEK_FILE)  base64-encoded 32-byte key-encryption key
# CUSTODIAN_KEYSTORE_DIR=/var/lib/catalog/keystore
# CUSTODIAN_KEK_FILE=/run/secrets/custodian_kek
#
# Reference harnesses only. The managed-KMS adapter (design O4) is still an open
# production deployment gate and would add another CUSTODIAN_MODE here. The planned
# age-encrypted-file KEK plugs into the KEK-resolution seam in the factory; it is NOT
# implemented in this stage.
